HEADWORD: Laconism
<hw>Lac"o*nism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr. <?/
to imitate Lacedaemonian manners, to speak laconically: cf. F.
<ets>laconisme</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A vigorous, brief manner
of expression; laconic style.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An instance of laconic style or
expression.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laconize</ent>⟦br⟧
